        "description": "<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you want to change the real estate market with us? Together we build the PropTech company of the future.<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>About Homeday and the Job Mission<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Homeday aims to improve the way people buy and sell real estate. Making the entire process simple, transparent, and more efficient. Together we have already saved our customers millions in commission.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Supporting users and guiding them efficiently through the processes involved in buying or selling real estate is a very important aspect. Therefore we, the Closing Squad, focus on the processes after buyers have been qualified as good and fitting the property. This includes booking the on-site viewing (OSV), the OSV itself, the feedback and offer-making process, the selection of a suitable buyer, and the \u00e2\u0080\u009cDigital Deal Closing\u00e2\u0080\u009d (DDC: the final steps to conclude a selling or buying).<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Stakeholder -<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Lars Feske (Engineering Manager)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Recruiter - <\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wolf-Martin Naumann (<\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/in\/wolf-martin-naumann-he-him-a40386188\/\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">LinkedIn<\/span><\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Contract -<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Full Time, unlimited<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Remote Policy - <\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Work 4 days from \u00e2\u0080\u009cwherever you are\u00e2\u0080\u009d and one Team-Day* in the office (*when the Covid situation allows it)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Location -<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Berlin or Cologne, Germany<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Where your expertise is needed<\/strong><strong><br><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Write clean and efficient code and follow best practices (TDD, CI, PRs, Code Reviews &amp; Standards) in an agile environment<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Continually introduce and integrate relevant new technologies.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Working closely with other developers and product designers to develop and test new ideas.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Your self organized attitude will help you to prioritize your tasks independently<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">manage business requirements and challenge them <\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br><br><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><strong>Closing - Squad - Context:<\/strong><strong><br><\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a Backend Engineer, you will be focussing on Homeday Connect, a customer relationship management (CRM) application that enables partner realtors from our brokerage business model as our one single source of truth of all documents and to keep everyone up to date about the status of deals. It is also used by our own back office team to manage deals, property-related data, buyer requests, and contacts in general. You will help the squad take meaningful actions based on the insights and analytical products to implement new, innovative features as well as maintain given ones.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>What we are looking for<\/strong><strong><br><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have a profound experience in Ruby and object-oriented development<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have a good knowledge of the Rails framework and Ruby ecosystem<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You work well with relational databases (MySQL and PostgreSQL)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You worked with third-party APIs and developed APIs yourself<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You have a strong testing background (RSpec, Minitest, etc.)<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You write meaningful and traceable Git commits<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You are familiar with agile development methods like SCRUM or KANBAN<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You are a great communicator, enjoy working in a team and paying attention to details<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You do not meet all of the points listed? No problem! Whether our expectations match, we will find out within a first call!<\/span><\/em><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>What we offer<\/strong><strong><br><\/strong><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Work-Life-Balance<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - You can work up to 80% of your time from home, choose part-time models and spend 30 days of vacation.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Advancement<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - You get 1000\u00e2\u0082\u00ac educational budget (+educational leave) yearly, biyearly feedback talks and annual salary increases.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Innovation<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - You work on products that revolutionize a conservative market.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>PropTech Company<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - We work with top notch technologies and you\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll work with the equipment of your choice.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Product Engineering Week<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - You\u00e2\u0080\u0099ll have the chance to work on anything you want for a week every quarter.<\/span><\/li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Relocation Support<\/strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> - If you need to move, we will support you to finance and organize your relocation.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>At Homeday, we don\u00e2\u0080\u0099t just accept diversity - we celebrate and support it! We\u00e2\u0080\u0099re committed to equal employment opportunities regardless of gender, place of origin, religion, age, sexual orientation, colour and disabilities. We care about each other!<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Our employees often refer to the 'Homeday Culture' as something special. We are proud they do \u00e2\u0080\u0093 as we are building and rebuilding it together everyday. At the core we are just a nice bunch of people. Working together on a mission. Guided by principles. Fair, diverse, transparent. Do you share our values? Then come and visit our teams for a glimpse of how Homeday works.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you have any questions in advance?<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Please contact our responsible Recruiter<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Wolf-Martin Naumann<\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br><\/span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">wolf.naumann@homeday.de<\/span><\/p>",
